{"_response_info":{"status":"ok"},"id":"https://www.gov.uk/api/angioplasty-and-driving.json","web_url":"https://www.gov.uk/angioplasty-and-driving","title":"Angioplasty and driving","format":"answer","details":{"need_id":"2210","business_proposition":false,"alternative_title":"","overview":"What you need to do about driving if you're had any type of angioplasty, including coronary or balloon angioplasty in your leg","body":"\n<div class=\"summary\">\n<p>You may need to tell <abbr title=\"Driver Vehicle and Licensing Agency\">DVLA</abbr> if you’ve had angioplasty.</p>\n</div>\n\n<div class=\"application-notice help-notice\">\n<p>You can be fined up to £1,000 if you don’t tell <abbr title=\"Driver Vehicle and Licensing Agency\">DVLA</abbr> about a medical condition that affects your driving. If you’re involved in an accident, you may be prosecuted.</p>\n</div>\n\n<h2>Car or motorcycle licence</h2>\n\n<p>You don&rsquo;t need to tell <abbr title=\"Driver Vehicle and Licensing Agency\">DVLA</abbr> that you&rsquo;ve had any type of angioplasty. </p>\n\n<p>However, you should stop driving for at least 1 week after this procedure and only start driving again when your doctor says that you are safe to do so.</p>\n\n<h2>Bus, coach or lorry licence</h2>\n\n<p>You must tell <abbr title=\"Driver Vehicle and Licensing Agency\">DVLA</abbr> if you&rsquo;ve had any type of angioplasty.</p>\n\n<p>Fill in form VOCH1 and send it to <abbr title=\"Driver Vehicle and Licensing Agency\">DVLA</abbr>. The address is on the form.</p>\n\n<div class=\"form-download\">\n<p><a href=\"http://www.direct.gov.uk/prod_consum_dg/groups/dg_digitalassets/@dg/@en/@motor/documents/digitalasset/dg_065302.pdf\" title=\"Download medical questionnaire\" rel=\"external\">Download ‘VOCH1 - Confidential medical information’ (PDF, 340KB)</a></p>\n</div>\n\n"},"updated_at":"2012-10-16T10:16:49+00:00","tags":[],"related":[{"id":"https://www.gov.uk/api/driving-if-disabled.json","web_url":"https://www.gov.uk/driving-if-disabled","title":"Medical conditions, disabilities and driving","format":"guide","details":{"need_id":"786","business_proposition":false},"updated_at":"2012-10-16T10:20:40+00:00"},{"id":"https://www.gov.uk/api/health-conditions-and-driving.json","web_url":"https://www.gov.uk/health-conditions-and-driving","title":"Health conditions and driving","format":"answer","details":{"need_id":"13","business_proposition":false},"updated_at":"2012-10-16T10:25:48+00:00"},{"id":"https://www.gov.uk/api/giving-up-your-driving-licence.json","web_url":"https://www.gov.uk/giving-up-your-driving-licence","title":"Giving up your driving licence","format":"answer","details":{"need_id":"2390","business_proposition":false},"updated_at":"2012-10-16T10:17:07+00:00"},{"id":"https://www.gov.uk/api/reapply-driving-licence-medical-condition.json","web_url":"https://www.gov.uk/reapply-driving-licence-medical-condition","title":"Re-apply for a driving licence following a medical condition","format":"answer","details":{"need_id":"2399","business_proposition":true},"updated_at":"2012-10-16T10:15:05+00:00"}]}